occurrenceRemarks: Tree 20 m tall; leaves subcoriaceous, deep green above, silvery below with fulvous brown midrib, revolute; young stems and petioles dull ferruginous as are pedicels and buds.

locality: Upstream from campsite, along stream. Meseta de Jaua: Cerro Jáua: cumbre de la porcióm Central-Occidental de la Meseta. Oeste, 36 miles nauticas o 60 km, noreste de la missión de Campamento Sanidade del Río Kanarakuni.
occurrenceRemarks: Shrub 2m; leaves rigid-coriaceous, dark green above, chocolate brown beneath on youngest leaves, grayish below on older leaves; calyx chocolate brown.
